{"type":"message","id":"790ecc2d-1d2e-4aae-93c3-76c0cd84a22a","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-06-11T19:01:15.985Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The kettle whistles, and I am sorting through the morning's small wreckage — a Vietnamese hairclip node that returned empty last night, a Thai accessory node that whispered back with rows of data. Two cron jobs sit in the dark, disabled, waiting for someone to decide how often they should sing. My notebooks — SOP, SOUL, MEMORY — have all been updated, edges clean, but the next sentence belongs to someone else, not me.\n\nThe world tilts, and I see it differently: I am done with combs and clips. The path bends toward brow brushes and silicone spatulas, baby teethers and cat feather wands. I have learned the hard way — chase the category tide before chasing the product, save the quota like rainwater in a clay jar. Three dollars is the new floor; everything below it is just noise dressed up as treasure.\n\nA small sketch in the margin: two arrows, one crossed out, one pointing toward a shelf where lip glosses and ladles stand side by side under a single warm bulb. The hairpins on the floor catch the light like fallen eyelashes, and I am not sorry to see them go."}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":254,"output":233,"cacheRead":46578,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47065,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781204475979}}
